ans%20are%20forced%20into%20the%20open%20and%20engaged%20in%20mobile%20warfare%2C%20the%20more%20tactically%20nimble%20Ukrainian%20troops%20might%20be%20able%20to%20destroy%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20strategy%20that%20Nazi%20Germany%20used%20with%20some%20success%20against%20the%20French%20in%201940%20and%20the%20Soviets%20in%201941%2C%20but%20it's%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%20Ukrainian%20troops%20have%20managed%20to%20penetrate%20the%20first%20of%20three%20Russian%20fortified%20belts%20in%20southern%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20the%20Russian%20military%20hasn't%20cracked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20handout%20photo%20taken%20from%20video%20released%20by%20Russian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Dec.%2022%2C%202022%2C%20Russian%20Defense%20Minister%20Sergei%20Shoigu%2C%20center%2C%20walks%20out%20of%20a%20trench%2C%20escorted%20by%20a%20group%20of%20officers%20as%20he%20inspects%20Russian%20troops%20at%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63d11b5c40fbb600192b5982%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20Defense%20Minister%20Sergei%20Shoigu%20exits%20a%20trench%20as%20he%20inspects%20troops%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20a%20photo%20released%20in%20December%202022.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Russian%20units%20can%20be%20forced%20to%20reposition%2C%20however%2C%20the%20poor%20training%20and%20discipline%20of%20Moscow's%20forces%20could%20see%20the%20defense%20become%20uncoordinated%20and%20susceptible%20to%20collapse%2C%26quot%3B%20experts%20with%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Fukraines-counteroffensive-begins-shall-leopards-break-free%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20June%2C%20as%20the%20counteroffensive%20was%20just%20beginning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20aggressive%20commanders%20like%20Gen.%20George%20Patton%20%E2%80%94%20who%20called%20fixed%20fortifications%20%26quot%3Bmonuments%20to%20the%20stupidity%20of%20man%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20an%20army%20that%20remains%20entrenched%20is%20an%20army%20that%20has%20handed%20the%20initiative%20to%20the%20enemy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20fortifications%20can%20also%20be%20a%20powerful%20force%20multiplier.%20While%20the%20Maginot%20Line%20is%20remembered%20as%20a%20fiasco%2C%20it%20was%20actually%20a%20reasonable%20way%20for%20France%20to%20economize%20on%20scarce%20manpower%20and%20free%20up%20troops%20for%20other%20sectors%20of%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20dynamic%20seems%20to%20be%20playing%20out%20in%20Ukraine%20today.%20Russian%20troops%20are%20dug%20into%20elaborate%20trench%20systems%20shielded%20by%20millions%20of%20mines%20and%20supported%20by%20artillery%20and%20attack%20helicopters.%20They%20have%20inflicted%20painful%20losses%20on%20Ukrainian%20assault%20brigades%20that%20are%20still%20learning%20to%20use%20their%20newly%20adopted%20Western%20tactics%20and%20armored%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20Bradley%20armored%20vehicle%20mechanics%20repair%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65032537992da60019ec6170%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20troops%20work%20on%20a%20US-made%20Bradley%20armored%20vehicle%20at%20a%20secret%20workshop%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20in%20July.%3Cp%3EEd%20Ram%2FFor%20The%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESecond-rate%20French%20divisions%20also%20inflicted%20heavy%20losses%20on%20German%20assault%20troops%20attempting%20to%20cross%20the%20Meuse%20River%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarfarehistorynetwork.com%2Farticle%2Fhow-second-battle-sedan-led-to-fall-of-france%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBattle%20of%20Sedan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%201940.%20While%20the%20French%20high%20command%20dithered%2C%20the%20battered%20defenders%20at%20Sedan%20eventually%20cracked%2C%20creating%20a%20hole%20that%20German%20armor%20swiftly%20exploited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20the%20campaign%20became%20a%20mobile%20field%20battle%2C%20which%20the%20rigid%20French%20command-and-control%20structure%20was%20unable%20to%20cope%20with.%20France%20%E2%80%94%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20military%20powers%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20surrendered%20in%20just%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accusation%20that%20French%20troops%20were%20cowardly%20is%20unfair.%20They%20often%20fought%20hard%20and%20bravely%2C%20but%20traumatized%20by%20the%20grievous%20losses%20of%20the%20First%20World%20War%2C%20their%20morale%20proved%20brittle.%20%26quot%3BAgain%20and%20again%20I%20have%20heard%20from%20tired%2C%20beaten%2C%20soured%20French%20soldiers%20the%20bitter%20words%3A%20'We%20were%20betrayed.%20The%20politicians%20sold%20us%20out%2C'%26quot%3B%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F1940%2F09%2Ffrance-in-june-the-collapse%2F654016%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20journalist%3C%2Fa%3E%20recalled%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20echoes%20with%20Russia%20in%202023%20are%20eerie.%20Russian%20soldiers%20frequently%20complain%20of%20incompetent%20commanders%20who%20callously%20sacrifice%20them%20in%20futile%20attacks.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-russia-uses-infantry-and-mercenaries-for-attacks-in-ukraine-2023-5%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BDisposable%20infantry%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20composed%20of%20prison%20inmates%20and%20reluctant%20conscripts%20are%20not%20likely%20to%20perform%20well%20during%20a%20retreat%2C%20perhaps%20the%20most%20stressful%20of%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20troops%20conscripts%20Omsk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65032536992da60019ec616d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20serviceman%20adjusts%20a%20conscript's%20uniform%20at%20a%20gathering%20point%20in%20Omsk%20in%20November%202022.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FAlexey%20Malgavko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20morale%20is%20%26quot%3Blow%2C%20with%20a%20rise%20in%20prosecutions%20for%20desertion%2C%20observed%20instances%20of%20wounded%20comrades%20being%20abandoned%2C%20and%20very%20little%20depth%20of%20junior%20leadership%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20RUSI%20report%20noted.%20%26quot%3BPersonnel%20are%20also%20rarely%20rotated%20and%20there%20is%20considerable%20weariness%20across%20the%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20despite%20hopes%20that%20Russian%20morale%20would%20collapse%20under%20Ukrainian%20assault%2C%20this%20hasn't%20happened%20on%20any%20significant%20scale.%20In%20theory%2C%20these%20problems%20%26quot%3Bshould%20make%20Russian%20units%20brittle%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20practice%2C%20they%20appear%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20very%20heavy%20punishment%20without%20collapsing.%20Instead%2C%20morale%20problems%20appear%20to%20manifest%20in%20poor%20cooperation%20within%20units%20and%20even%20less%20between%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20for%20Ukraine%20is%20that%20Russian%20forces%20suffer%20from%20%26quot%3Ba%20tendency%20for%20coordination%20and%20cohesion%20to%20fracture%20under%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20added.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20likely%20to%20make%20Russian%20units%20underperform%20in%20defense