or-but-no-evidence-any-sightings-have-been-alien-in-origin-12961093%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Temples%20Can't%20Be%20Used%20for%20Politics%3A%20Kerala%20HC%20Dismisses%20Plea%20Seeking%20Permit%20to%20Erect%20Saffron%20Flags%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FKerala-HC.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Kerala%20high%20court%20has%20dismissed%20a%20petition%20seeking%20permission%20to%20erect%20saffron%20flags%20on%20a%20temple%2C%20observing%20that%20temples%20cannot%20be%20used%20for%20political%20one-upmanship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTemples%20stand%20as%20beacons%20of%20spiritual%20solace%20and%20tranquility%2C%20their%20sanctity%20and%20reverence%20being%20of%20paramount%20importance.%20Such%20hallowed%20spiritual%20grounds%20must%20not%20be%20diminished%20by%20political%20maneuverings%20or%20attempts%20at%20one-upmanship.%20%E2%80%A6The%20actions%20and%20intentions%20of%20the%20petitioners%20are%20clearly%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20serene%20and%20sacred%20atmosphere%20to%20be%20maintained%20in%20the%20temple%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%20news%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala-high-court-rejects-plea-saffron-flags-temple%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20court%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20claiming%20to%20be%20devotees%20of%20the%20Muthupilakkadu%20Sree%20Parthasarathy%20temple%20wanted%20to%20put%20up%20flags%20on%20the%20temple.%20They%20alleged%20that%20their%20attempts%20to%20put%20saffron%20flags%20on%20the%20temple%20premises%20during%20special%20occasions%20and%20festivals%20were%20obstructed%20by%20the%20respondents%2C%20allegedly%20using%20their%20political%20links.%20According%20to%20the%20petitioners%2C%20they%20formed%20an%20organisation%20in%202022%20called%20%E2%80%98Parthasarathy%20Bakthajanasamithi%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20aimed%20at%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20temple%20and%20its%20devotees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20Kerala%20government%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20argued%20that%20allowing%20the%20petitioners%20to%20put%20up%20flags%20and%20festoons%20associated%20with%20a%20certain%20political%20party%20would%20be%20tantamount%20to%20%E2%80%9Callowing%20the%20temple%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20battleground%20for%20political%20one-upmanship%E2%80%9D.%20The%20government%20also%20alleged%20that%20there%20were%20numerous%20clashes%20on%20the%20temple%20premises%20earlier%20due%20to%20the%20actions%20of%20petitioners.%20One%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20the%20government%20alleged%2C%20is%20also%20involved%20in%20multiple%20criminal%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20brought%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20court%20that%20the%20temple%E2%80%99s%20administrative%20committee%20had%20passed%20a%20resolution%20banning%20the%20installation%20of%20flags%2C%20banners%2C%20among%20others%2C%20of%20any%20political%20parties%20or%20organisations%20within%20a%20radius%20of%20100%20meters%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EKanikkavanchi%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20also%20drew%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20court%20that%20in%202020%2C%20it%20had%20directed%20the%20police%20to%20remove%20any%20such%20installation%20from%20temple%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20hearing%20various%20sides%2C%20the%20court%20in%20its%20ruling%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20petitioners%20have%20not%20demonstrated%20any%20legitimate%20authority%20to%20conduct%20temple%20rituals%20as%20they%20have%20prayed%20for.%20Furthermore%2C%20they%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20erect%20flags%20or%20festoons%20in%20or%20around%20the%20temple%2C%20in%20light%20of%20the%20orders%20issued%20by%20this%20Court%20and%20decision%20taken%20by%20the%20administrative%20committee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694689522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuplo